abebooks-rare-used-books.longDescription:
## AbeBooks Rare & Used Books API

Access AbeBooks marketplace data from thousands of independent booksellers worldwide.

### Features
- Search rare, antiquarian, used & out-of-print books
- Returns title, author, ISBN, price, condition, edition, publisher, year, binding type
- Seller details and listing information
- Up to 50 results per search, structured JSON

### Built For
Developers building rare book price trackers, collection management tools, library acquisition systems, book dealer sourcing platforms, and academic research tools.

### Example Use
Query `?q=first edition hemingway&sort=price` → returns rare Hemingway editions with pricing, condition, and seller details.

**Free tier**: 50 requests/month.

## Code Examples

### cURL
```bash
# Search by ISBN for a specific rare book
curl -X GET 'https://abebooks-rare-used-books.p.rapidapi.com/abebooks/search?query=9780743273565&limit=10' \
  -H 'X-RapidAPI-Key: YOUR_RAPIDAPI_KEY' \
  -H 'X-RapidAPI-Host: abebooks-rare-used-books.p.rapidapi.com'
```

### Python
```python
import requests

url = 'https://abebooks-rare-used-books.p.rapidapi.com/abebooks/search'
# Find rare first editions of The Great Gatsby
params = {
    'query': 'first edition great gatsby',
    'limit': '10'
}
headers = {
    'X-RapidAPI-Key': 'YOUR_RAPIDAPI_KEY',
    'X-RapidAPI-Host': 'abebooks-rare-used-books.p.rapidapi.com'
}

response = requests.get(url, headers=headers, params=params)
books = response.json()
for book in books.get('results', []):
    print(f"{book['title']} by {book['author']} - ${book['price']} ({book['condition']}) - ISBN: {book.get('isbn', 'N/A')}")
```

### JavaScript
```javascript
const options = {
  method: 'GET',
  headers: {
    'X-RapidAPI-Key': 'YOUR_RAPIDAPI_KEY',
    'X-RapidAPI-Host': 'abebooks-rare-used-books.p.rapidapi.com'
  }
};

// Look up antiquarian books by author
fetch('https://abebooks-rare-used-books.p.rapidapi.com/abebooks/search?query=signed+tolkien+lord+of+the+rings&limit=10', options)
  .then(res => res.json())
  .then(data => {
    data.results.forEach(book => {
      console.log(`${book.title} (${book.year}) - $${book.price} - ${book.condition} - ${book.seller}`);
    });
  });
```

